{"questionId":"6bfd0c2e-65a8-46f9-a800-10203b4c8d45_22","correctAnswer":"C","section":"Math","steps":[{"title":"Set up","content":"Vertex at $(1,7)$ gives vertex form $f(x) = a(x-1)^2 + 7$. Use the point $(2,53)$ to find $a$."},{"title":"Solve","content":"Substitute: $a(2-1)^2 + 7 = 53 \\Rightarrow a = 46$. Now compute: $$f(-2) = 46(-3)^2 + 7 = 414 + 7 = 421$$ $$f(0) = 46(-1)^2 + 7 = 46 + 7 = 53$$ $$f(-2) - f(0) = 421 - 53 = 368$$"},{"title":"Answer","content":"<strong>C</strong> is correct.","desmosExpressions":["f(x) = 46(x-1)^2 + 7","(1, 7)","(2, 53)","(-1, 191)"]}]}